  "texts": [
    "We build an index using each strategy on Deep1M and Deep25GB and measure distance calculations.",
    "We calculate the distance overhead of SN compared to KS, and we estimate the number of additional 100-NN queries that the KS-based graph can answer, with 0.99 recall, before the SN-based graph completes its construction.",
    "We observe (Table 2) that the SN-based graph requires 182 million and 22.3 billion more distance calculations than the KS-based graph on Deep1M and Deep25GB respectively.",
    "Furthermore, the KS-based graph can answer 45K and 1.17 million queries on Deep1M and Deep25GB respectively before the SN-based graph finishes construction.",
    "Indexing PerformanceWe evaluate twelve state-of-the-art vector search methods, varying dataset sizes and reporting total indexing time and memory footprint."
